explains: adj. 无印记的（没有印象的），不感兴趣的

sentences.en: He was also very unimpressed by his teachers.
sentences.cn: 他也没觉得他的老师们有多好。

sentences.en: Kitty's family was unworldly, unimpressed by power or money.
sentences.cn: 基蒂的家庭淡泊物质，不为权利和金钱所动。

sentences.en: He appeared unimpressed; but then, unimpressed was his default state.
sentences.cn: 他看似不为所动，但是，不为所动就是他的原样。
